## 10. Interfaces & Dependencies
[COMPANY] **shall** document the interfaces between in-scope and out-of-scope elements and the third-party dependencies relied upon (e.g., [AWS] and [Snowflake] as subservice organizations, [GitHub] as a build dependency). Subservice and vendor reliance is managed under `../vendor/third-party-risk-management-policy.md.template`, including Business Associate Agreements where PHI is processed.

## 11. Exceptions
Exceptions to this statement (e.g., a temporary inclusion or exclusion) require documented risk acceptance per `exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer] and [CEO], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 12. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Scope accuracy is verified through the asset inventory process, internal audit (`internal-audit-program.md.template`), and management review. Material drift between documented scope and actual environment is treated as a finding and tracked to closure per `corrective-action-poam.md.template`. Operating PHI-handling activities outside the defined scope is a policy violation handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

